& [IntendedPurpose] is the mathematical target shape
  + [purpose] is prove that for every compact simple gauge group G, a nontrivial quantum Yang-Mills theory exists on four-dimensional space-time and has a positive mass gap
  + [existence_core] is construct a rigorous quantum field theory satisfying axioms at least as strong as the cited constructive or axiomatic QFT frameworks
  + [gap_core] is prove that the Hamiltonian or energy spectrum has no nonzero states arbitrarily close to the vacuum
  + [authority_floor] is a construction of the theory plus a spectral lower-bound proof

& [DocumentProposition] is the source-implied proposition
  + [raw_shape] is mass is sealed curvature, glyphic enclosure, or symbolic encryption that resists unfolding without the correct resonance key
  + [candidate_receptive_form] is localized stable excitations may arise from nonabelian field self-interaction, confinement-like structure, or spectral separation
  + [meaning_role] is heuristic for why a positive mass scale might emerge from field structure
  + [proof_status] is inquiry_candidate_not_proof

& [SymbolicToFormalMap] is the first translation
